		<p>Courses that have been taught include:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Irrigation System Design, Evaluation and Scheduling</li>
			<li>Small Scale Irrigation Design and Management</li>
			<li>Irrigation Water Production Functions</li>
			<li>Pumping for Irrigation and Drainage</li>
			<li>Interdisciplinary Crop Production Management</li>
			<li>Crop Production Technologies</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Agro Engineering has provided applied agricultural training under contract for such entities as the International Irrigation Center of Utah State University, U.S. Peace Corps, U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID), and the InterAmerican Development Bank. Our consultants have trained students from developing and developed countries. Courses are taught bilingually (English/Spanish). We have coordinated, conducted and/or provided instructors for over 30 short courses in the U.S. and overseas.</p>
		<p>Agro Engineering consultants have developed training materials on irrigation, hillside irrigation, agro forestry, soil fertility, pest management, and farm economics among others. We have developed a comprehensive irrigation training and reference manual for the U.S. Peace Corps. We have also developed training materials dealing with water management for USAID, the International Irrigation Center and others.</p>
